msgid "media-down"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../netlink/specs/dpll.yaml:55
msgid ""
"dpll device lock status was changed because of associated media got down. "
"This may happen for example if dpll device was previously locked on an input "
"pin of type PIN_TYPE_SYNCE_ETH_PORT."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../netlink/specs/dpll.yaml:0
msgid "fractional-frequency-offset-too-high"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../netlink/specs/dpll.yaml:55
msgid ""
"the FFO (Fractional Frequency Offset) between the RX and TX symbol rate on "
"the media got too high. This may happen for example if dpll device was "
"previously locked on an input pin of type PIN_TYPE_SYNCE_ETH_PORT."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../netlink/specs/dpll.yaml:89
msgid "clock-quality-level"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../netlink/specs/dpll.yaml:89
msgid ""
"level of quality of a clock device. This mainly applies when the dpll lock-"
"status is DPLL_LOCK_STATUS_HOLDOVER. The current list is defined according "
"to the table 11-7 contained in ITU-T G.8264/Y.1364 document. One may extend "
"this list freely by other ITU-T defined clock qualities, or different ones "
"defined by another standardization body (for those, please use different "
"prefix)."
